Program: Outlook
Title: Outlook Weekend: 3067 Metres and Falling
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cstzb9
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 2 Oct 2017
Kevin Hines is among the one per cent of people who've jumped off the Golden Gate Bridge and survived both the 67-metre fall and the freezing water. In 1984, the athletes Mary Decker and Zola Budd were caught up in one of the most controversial moments in Olympic history during the 3000-metre track final. They were reunited 32 years later for a documentary about that incident called The Fall. (Photo: Man Falling Off Office Building Roof with Birds Flying. Credit: DrGrounds/Getty Images) Show less